comment: * A class that contains Web Trigger Event data sent from the Measurement API to the * OnDevicePersonalization service when the browser registers a web trigger * with the * Measurement API and the web trigger data is intended to be processed by an * {@link IsolatedService}. * @hide

variables.name: mDestinationUrl
variables.comment: * The URL of the web page where the web trigger event occurred.

variables.name: mAppPackageName
variables.comment: * The package name of the browser app where the web trigger event occurred.

variables.name: mIsolatedService
variables.comment:
* The package and class name of the {@link IsolatedService} that should process
     * the web trigger event.

variables.name: mCertDigest
variables.comment:
* An optional SHA-256 hash of the signing key of the package that contains
     * the {@link IsolatedService}, to guard against package name spoofing via sideloading.
     * If this field is present and does not match the signing key of the installed receiver
     * service package, the web trigger event is discarded.

variables.name: mEventData
variables.comment:
* Additional data that the server may provide to the {@link IsolatedService}. This can be
     * {@code null} if the server does not need to provide any data other than the required fields.

methods.comment: * The URL of the web page where the web trigger event occurred.
